(
<emphasis box="[584,601,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[625,759,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">nemorivaga</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Moriuti" box="[766,926,1555,1580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Moriuti, S. (1969) Argyresthiidae (Lepidoptera) of Japan. Bulletin of the University of Osaka Prefecture, Series B, 21, 1 ‾ 50." type="journal article" year="1969">Moriuti, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[989,1087,1555,1580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1935" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idiograpta" subGenus="Blastotere">
<emphasis box="[1126,1150,1555,1578]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1167,1191,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1208,1326,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">idiograpta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Caradja, A. &amp; Meyrick, E. (1935) Materialien zu einer Microlepidopteren-fauna der Chinesischen Provinzen Kiangsu, Chekiang und Hunan. R. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, 96 pp., 2 pls." type="book" year="1935">Meyrick, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
resembles species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[627,741,1591,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Blastotere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[627,741,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Blastotere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having forewing R4 and R5 stalked (
<bibRefCitation author="Caradja" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Caradja, A. &amp; Meyrick, E. (1935) Materialien zu einer Microlepidopteren-fauna der Chinesischen Provinzen Kiangsu, Chekiang und Hunan. R. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, 96 pp., 2 pls." type="book" year="1935">Caradja &amp; Meyrick 1935</bibRefCitation>
), and it is thus tentatively placed in this subgenus. 
<taxonomicName authority="Moriuti, 1969" authorityName="Moriuti" authorityYear="1969" box="[787,1256,1629,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonica" subGenus="Blastotere">
<emphasis box="[787,917,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Argyresthia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[934,958,1630,1653]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[975,1073,1630,1653]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">japonica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moriuti" box="[1088,1248,1629,1654]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Moriuti, S. (1969) Argyresthiidae (Lepidoptera) of Japan. Bulletin of the University of Osaka Prefecture, Series B, 21, 1 ‾ 50." type="journal article" year="1969">Moriuti, 1969</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is distinctive in the genitalia, and is tentatively placed in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[774,888,1666,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Blastotere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[774,888,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Blastotere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
considering the characters of the socius and the valva, and particularly of the phallus with strong denticles in the male genitalia.
